<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
    ServiceNow Update Set record-definition for the `sys_dictionary` row that
    declares the `description` String field on the `x_[scope]_case` custom
    table inside the scoped application `x_[scope]`.

    Per AAP Section 0.5.7 (Data-Model Mapping verbatim):
        Field        Type           Constraints
        description  String(4000)   Mandatory

    Per AAP Section 0.4.4 the case-submission portal page populates this
    field as one of the five user-supplied inputs:
        "Page 1 - Case Submission: a simple form with five inputs
        (subject, type, description, requester_name, requester_email)."
    The submission widget binds the textarea input to this field and passes
    its value through the scripted REST submission endpoint, which performs
    a GlideRecord.insert() against `x_[scope]_case` with the user-supplied
    description literal.

    Per AAP Section 0.7.4 ("Portal lookup output filtering") this field is
    EXPLICITLY NOT exposed by the case-status-lookup endpoint - the lookup
    returns ONLY status, subject, opened_date - no internal fields exposed.
    Description is treated as INTERNAL because:
      (a) free-form descriptions can contain sensitive narrative detail that
          MUST NOT be returned to anonymous callers performing a case-number
          lookup; and
      (b) AAP Section 0.7.4 enumerates exactly THREE whitelisted lookup
          fields, and description is not among them.
    This intentional omission is enforced at the response-payload level by
    the lookup endpoint's CasePortalService.lookupCase() helper, which
    constructs a JSON object containing only the three permitted columns.

    Semantic source-side reference (read-only, NOT byte-for-byte ported):
      - acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-case-file-plugin/src/main/java/
        com/armedia/acm/plugins/casefile/model/CaseFile.java lines 144-146:
            @Lob
            @Column(name = "cm_case_details")
            private String details;
        ArkCase's `details` field was a JPA Large Object (`@Lob`) String
        column on `acm_case_file` mapped to physical column
        `cm_case_details`. JPA `@Lob` on a String maps to the database-
        engine TEXT/LONGTEXT type (effectively unbounded - up to 4 GB on
        MySQL InnoDB). Per AAP Section 0.1.2, the ServiceNow target
        intentionally caps the equivalent column at 4000 chars to keep
        the schema bounded and predictable for a POC; unbounded LOB
        storage on a scoped table is not justified by the POC's data
        volumes and would require special handling on the form, in the
        scripted REST endpoint, and in dashboards.
      - The field name is RENAMED from ArkCase's `details` to ServiceNow's
        `description` per AAP Section 0.5.7 verbatim. This is an
        INTENTIONAL rename: AAP Section 0.5.1 lists the target field as
        `description`, and `description` is the conventional ServiceNow
        long-form text column name (e.g., task.description,
        incident.description, change_request.description). The rename
        aligns the POC schema with platform-native naming so OOB form
        layouts, list-view column choosers, and report-grouping UIs all
        recognize the column as the long-form descriptive narrative.
      - ArkCase's CaseFile also had a sibling `caseDetailsSummary` field
        (lines 148-150, also `@Lob` String mapped to `cm_case_details_summary`).
        That sibling is NOT replicated in the POC: AAP Section 0.5.7's
        case schema lists only `description`, not a separate summary
        column. The POC accepts a single descriptive field per case, and
        any summarization is delegated to the user when populating
        `subject` (the short summary in ./x_[scope]_case_subject.xml).
      - Bean Validation: ArkCase's `details` carried no @Size, @NotNull,
        or @NotEmpty annotations - it was technically nullable. The POC
        UPGRADES this to mandatory=true per AAP Section 0.5.7 verbatim
        ("description | String(4000) | Mandatory"). A case with no
        description is rejected at every entry point: the internal form
        (platform-native mandatory enforcement), the Table API, the
        scripted REST submission endpoint (which surfaces a 400-class
        error to the portal), and seed scripts (which fail to insert).

    Constraints honored (AAP Sections 0.7.1, 0.7.2, 0.7.4):
      - Scope-namespace exclusivity: `<name>` resolves to `x_[scope]_case`
        within the scoped application, and `<sys_scope>` / `<sys_package>`
        bind THIS dictionary record to the same scope by `source` attribute
        lookup. NO global-scope writes - the OOB tables `task`, `incident`,
        `sys_user`, etc. are never modified.
      - Zero hardcoded cross-reference sys_ids: the `<sys_scope>` and
        `<sys_package>` text-node values resolve by scope source name
        (`x_[scope]`), not by literal sys_id. The `<sys_id>`
        text-node value is THIS record's own deterministic primary key
        (MD5 of the canonical field identifier `x_[scope]_case.description`)
        and is NOT a reference to any other record. The MD5 derivation
        guarantees that re-generation of this Update Set on any agent run
        produces a byte-identical `<sys_id>` (no random UUIDs), which is
        required for clean Update-Set re-import on a fresh PDI without
        creating duplicate sys_dictionary rows. Verified:
            python3 -c "import hashlib; print(hashlib.md5(b'x_[scope]_case.description').hexdigest())"
        prints 548ff520bd22f86da39916a86f8cef1e (matches sys_id below).
      - The literal `[scope]` placeholder is preserved per AAP convention;
        the PDI auto-assigns the actual scope id at App Engine Studio
        creation time. The placeholder appears in `<name>`, `<sys_scope>`,
        `<sys_package>`, and `<sys_update_name>` consistently.
      - mandatory=true at the dictionary level (AAP Section 0.5.7 verbatim:
        "description | String(4000) | Mandatory"). This MUST hold across
        all four insert paths into `x_[scope]_case`:
          (1) the internal form - the platform's form-layout engine renders
              an asterisk and refuses to save without a value;
          (2) the Table API (PUT/POST) - the platform returns a 400 with
              "field is mandatory" if missing;
          (3) the scripted REST submission endpoint - the endpoint's
              field-validation pre-check rejects an empty description
              before invoking GlideRecord.insert() and returns a structured
              400 to the portal so the submission widget can display an
              inline error;
          (4) the seed-data scripts - all 10 demo cases populate this
              field with non-PII synthetic narratives.
      - read_only=false: internal users with the case_manager role may
        amend or extend the description after submission (e.g., to
        consolidate later context); case_agent role users on assigned
        cases may also extend per AAP Section 0.5.6 ACL matrix. Internal-
        user write authorization is governed by the table-level ACLs in
        ../acl/ - this dictionary entry deliberately does NOT carry
        per-role write_roles since the table-level ACLs apply uniformly
        across all editable fields.
      - default_value is EMPTY (no implicit default) per AAP Section 0.5.7
        and the agent prompt's Phase 4 verbatim. Defaulting silently to
        a placeholder string ("(no description)") would silently mask
        submissions that failed mandatory enforcement and pollute later
        report grouping or text searches.
      - audit=false per AAP Section 0.3.1 minimal-change clause. The
        status field on this same table carries audit=true because every
        state transition must be reconstructable post-hoc; description is
        long-form descriptive metadata, not a regulated lifecycle
        attribute, so the additional sys_audit row per update is
        unnecessary overhead for a POC. (Storing a 4000-char column in
        sys_audit per update would also amplify the audit-trail volume
        considerably for what is effectively descriptive content.)
      - max_length=4000 EXACTLY per AAP Section 0.5.7 verbatim. NOT 4096,
        NOT unlimited (`@Lob` in ArkCase was effectively unbounded), NOT
        255 (subject, the short summary), NOT 100 (requester_name,
        requester_email). The 4000-char cap is a deliberate POC
        simplification per AAP Section 0.1.2 that:
          (i) keeps the platform-native string column type (no large-
              object handling, no streaming, no CLOB semantics);
          (ii) renders cleanly in the OOB form-layout text-area;
          (iii) fits comfortably within typical case-narrative volumes
                without truncation in practice;
          (iv) avoids platform-specific tunings required for very large
               text storage on scoped tables.
      - internal_type=string is correct for fields up to 4000 chars in
        ServiceNow. The platform's form engine automatically renders a
        String column with max_length > 255 as a multi-line text-area on
        the form layout (no `attributes` override required for the text-
        area presentation itself). For larger content, alternative
        internal_types like `string_full_utf8` would apply, but at 4000
        chars the standard `string` type is correct.
      - choice=0 = "Free-form String, no choice list". Description is
        unconstrained natural-language text; constraining it to a choice
        list would defeat its purpose as a free-form narrative.
      - unique=false: multiple cases may legitimately share the same
        description (e.g., a recurring complaint pattern across many
        requesters). Uniqueness at the case level is delegated entirely
        to the auto-generated `number` field per AAP Section 0.5.7
        (./x_[scope]_case_number.xml carries unique=true).
      - text_index=true future-proofs basic full-text search across the
        case list / dashboards. Description is the highest-content
        free-form String on x_[scope]_case and is the most likely target
        for keyword search by internal users investigating recurring
        themes. The cost of indexing is negligible at POC data volumes
        (10 demo cases) and AAP gate 6 (Dashboards) does not require
        keyword search, so text_index is harmless.
      - spell_check=true is appropriate for a long-form free-form text
        input. The platform surfaces inline spell-check suggestions on
        the form text-area, improving UX without affecting persistence.
      - attributes=edge_encryption_enabled=true per the agent prompt's
        Phase 6 directive. This dictionary attribute marks the column as
        eligible for ServiceNow Edge Encryption when the feature is
        configured at the instance level. On a vanilla PDI without Edge
        Encryption configured, this attribute is recognized but inactive
        (it does not affect persistence, form rendering, or Update Set
        preview), so it is a safe forward-compatibility annotation. It
        also matches the OOB convention for long-form descriptive
        columns on platform tables (e.g., task.description, which
        carries similar attributes on its dictionary row).
      - No reference target: this is a free-form String field, not a
        Reference field. All `<reference*>` elements are empty and
        `<table_reference>false</table_reference>`.
      - No PII: while the field stores synthetic case-narrative phrases
        in the demo seed data, NO real names, real email addresses,
        real phone numbers, real organization names, or real case
        content from the source ArkCase database are placed in this
        column at any point in the build (per AAP Section 0.3.2
        synthetic-data-only constraint). Demo seed values are
        fabricated narratives such as "Synthetic complaint regarding
        delayed processing of a benefits inquiry" or "General question
        about service availability".

    Cross-references (AAP Section 0.5.2 dependency ordering):
      - This record MUST load AFTER `../tables/x_[scope]_case.xml`
        (parent table), since `<name>x_[scope]_case</name>` references
        the table by name.
      - This record MUST load BEFORE the consumers that read or write
        the `description` column:
          * ../portal/rest/sys_ws_definition_x_[scope]_case_submit.xml
            (the scripted REST submission endpoint - writes this field
            from the user's portal-form input on every anonymous case
            submission; AAP Section 0.4.4 lists `description` as one of
            the five user-supplied inputs the page collects)
          * ../portal/widgets/sp_widget_x_[scope]_case_submission_widget.xml
            (the submission widget binds its description text-area input
            to this field via the scripted REST submission endpoint)
          * ../script_includes/x_[scope]_CasePortalService.xml
            (the submitCase() helper method writes this field on behalf
            of the scripted REST submission endpoint)
          * ../seed-data/cases/x_[scope]_case_demo_*.xml (synthetic
            demo cases that MUST populate this mandatory field with
            realistic non-PII narratives to satisfy AAP Section 0.7.4
            minimum-data threshold of "at least 10 cases across all
            statuses, both case types represented")

      - This record is EXPLICITLY NOT consumed by:
          * ../portal/rest/sys_ws_definition_x_[scope]_case_status_lookup.xml
            (the scripted REST status-lookup endpoint - per AAP Section
            0.7.4, the lookup returns ONLY status, subject, opened_date;
            description is treated as internal and MUST NOT appear in
            the response payload). Implementations of the lookup endpoint
            MUST whitelist exactly status, subject, opened_date when
            constructing the response object - any leakage of description
            is a portal-data-exposure violation per AAP Section 0.7.4.
          * ../portal/widgets/sp_widget_x_[scope]_case_lookup_widget.xml
            (consumes only the three whitelisted fields returned by the
            lookup endpoint).
-->
<record_update table="sys_dictionary">
    <sys_dictionary action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <array>false</array>
        <attributes>edge_encryption_enabled=true</attributes>
        <audit>false</audit>
        <calculation/>
        <choice>0</choice>
        <choice_field/>
        <choice_table/>
        <column_label>Description</column_label>
        <comments>Mandatory String(4000) capturing the full case description. Populated by the case_submit scripted REST endpoint from the portal submission page. NOT exposed by case_status_lookup per AAP Section 0.7.4. Replaces ArkCase CaseFile.details (@Lob String, intentionally bounded at 4000 chars).</comments>
        <create_roles/>
        <default_value/>
        <defaultsort/>
        <delete_roles/>
        <dependent/>
        <dependent_on_field/>
        <display>true</display>
        <dynamic_creation>false</dynamic_creation>
        <dynamic_creation_script/>
        <dynamic_default_value/>
        <dynamic_ref_qual/>
        <element>description</element>
        <element_reference>false</element_reference>
        <foreign_database/>
        <function_definition/>
        <function_field>false</function_field>
        <internal_type>string</internal_type>
        <mandatory>true</mandatory>
        <max_length>4000</max_length>
        <name>x_[scope]_case</name>
        <next_element/>
        <primary>false</primary>
        <read_only>false</read_only>
        <read_roles/>
        <reference/>
        <reference_cascade_rule/>
        <reference_floor/>
        <reference_key/>
        <reference_qual/>
        <reference_qual_condition/>
        <reference_type/>
        <sizeclass/>
        <spell_check>true</spell_check>
        <staged>false</staged>
        <sys_class_name>sys_dictionary</sys_class_name>
        <sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by>
        <sys_created_on>2025-01-01 00:00:00</sys_created_on>
        <sys_id>548ff520bd22f86da39916a86f8cef1e</sys_id>
        <sys_mod_count>0</sys_mod_count>
        <sys_name/>
        <sys_package display_value="Case Management" source="x_[scope]">x_[scope]</sys_package>
        <sys_policy/>
        <sys_scope display_value="Case Management">x_[scope]</sys_scope>
        <sys_update_name>sys_dictionary_x_[scope]_case_description</sys_update_name>
        <sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by>
        <sys_updated_on>2025-01-01 00:00:00</sys_updated_on>
        <table_reference>false</table_reference>
        <text_index>true</text_index>
        <unique>false</unique>
        <use_dependent_field>false</use_dependent_field>
        <use_dynamic_default>false</use_dynamic_default>
        <use_reference_qualifier>simple</use_reference_qualifier>
        <virtual>false</virtual>
        <virtual_type/>
        <widget/>
        <write_roles/>
        <xml_view>false</xml_view>
    </sys_dictionary>
</record_update>
